Key Features

A service provisioning call will create a PostgreSQL database. Each service instance connects to a single database that is secure from other databases on the server.
A binding call will return a database uri that can be used to connect to the database.
Unbinding calls will disable the database user role when there are no other bindings.
Deprovisioning calls will delete all resources created.

